reviewer_codex_review.task_prompt:
Repository: {repository}
Entity: {entity_key}
IngressEvent: {ingress_event_type}
PRTitle: {pull_title}
PRState: {pull_state}
BaseRef: {pull_base_ref}
HeadRef: {pull_head_ref}
ChangedFiles: {pull_changed_files}
Additions: {pull_additions}
Deletions: {pull_deletions}
Commits: {pull_commits}
PRBody: {pull_body}
DiffFilesIncluded: {reviewer_diff_file_count}
PullRequestDiffContext:
{reviewer_diff_context}
Task: Perform a concrete code review and return JSON only.
Use the provided pull request diff context as source of truth.
Do not run shell commands, filesystem reads, or network calls.
Do not state that access is unavailable when DiffFilesIncluded is greater than zero.
Reference concrete file paths from PullRequestDiffContext in every comment.
Every comment must map to right-side diff lines only.
Output JSON object format exactly:
{{"summary":"<short review summary>","comments":[{{"path":"<file path>","line":123,"side":"RIGHT","body":"<inline review comment>"}}]}}
If there are no actionable findings, return comments as an empty list.

